The management of Gombe United football club under the leadership of Alhaji Ahmed Usman (Mabrook) has declared a two week break for the players,National Daily learnt.
This is  to allow  Muslim brothers celebrate the Eid -el fitr with their families and love ones at home ,in addition watching the 2018 FIFA World Cup which will kick off  Thursday in Russia.
However, players are warned not to exceed the resumption date which is Tuesday 26/6/18 in order to have ample time to prepare well for the remaining #NNL18  fixtures.
The management wishes them a happy Sallah celebrations  and pray that Nigeria will  become the first African country to reach the final and even the  Mundial.
